# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok secretary-general kofi annan dismissed the iraqi parliament 's opposition to the tough new u.n. resolution and said tuesday that he hopes the government will accept the security council 's plan to resume u.n. weapons inspections .
# ::alignments
(a / and
      :op1 (d / dismiss-01
            :ARG0 (p / person
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Kofi"
                        :op2 "Annan")
                  :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                        :ARG2 (s / secretary
                              :mod (g / general))))
            :ARG1 (o / oppose-01
                  :ARG0 (g2 / government-organization
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Parliament")
                        :mod (c / country
                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "Iraq")))
                  :ARG1 (r / resolution
                        :mod (o2 / organization
                              :name (n4 / name
                                    :op1 "U.N."))
                        :ARG1-of (n5 / new-01)
                        :ARG1-of (t / tough-02))))
      :op2 (s2 / say-01
            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (h2 / hope-01
                  :ARG0 p
                  :ARG1 (a2 / accept-01
                        :ARG0 (g3 / government-organization
                              :ARG0-of (g4 / govern-01))
                        :ARG1 (p2 / plan-01
                              :ARG0 (c2 / council
                                    :mod (s3 / security))
                              :ARG1 (r2 / resume-01
                                    :ARG0 c2
                                    :ARG1 (ii / inspect-01
                                          :ARG1 (w / weapon))))))
            :time (d2 / date-entity
                  :weekday (t2 / tuesday))))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok kenya 's mediators who are trying to broker peace between feuding political parties said a deal could be struck within the next ## to ## hours .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :ARG0-of (m / mediate-01)
            :poss (c / country
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Kenya"))
            :ARG0-of (t / try-01
                  :ARG1 (b / broker-01
                        :ARG0 p
                        :ARG1 (p2 / peace)
                        :ARG2 (p3 / party
                              :ARG0-of (f / feud-01)
                              :mod (p4 / politics)))))
      :ARG1 (p5 / possible-01
            :ARG1 (s2 / strike-01
                  :ARG1 (d / deal-01)
                  :time (a / after
                        :op1 (n2 / now)
                        :quant (u / up-to
                              :op1 (h / hour))))))

# ::id 2 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok republican vice presidential candidate sarah palin has agreed to sit down with abc news later this week for her first television interview since john mccain chose her as his running mate more than a week ago .
# ::alignments
(a / agree-01
      :ARG0 (c / candidate
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Sarah"
                  :op2 "Palin")
            :mod (p / president
                  :mod (v / vice))
            :mod (p2 / political-party
                  :name (n2 / name
                        :op1 "Republican")))
      :ARG1 (s / sit-down-02
            :ARG1 c
            :ARG2 (p3 / publication
                  :name (n3 / name
                        :op1 "ABC"
                        :op2 "News"))
            :time (a2 / after)
            :time (w / week
                  :mod (t / this))
            :purpose (ii / interview-01
                  :ARG0 p3
                  :ARG1 c
                  :medium (t2 / television)
                  :ord (o / ordinal-entity
                        :value 1
                        :range (s2 / since
                              :op1 (c2 / choose-01
                                    :ARG0 (p4 / person
                                          :name (n4 / name
                                                :op1 "John"
                                                :op2 "McCain"))
                                    :ARG1 c
                                    :ARG4 (h / have-rel-role-91
                                          :ARG0 p4
                                          :ARG1 p4
                                          :ARG2 (r / running-mate))
                                    :time (b / before
                                          :op1 (n5 / now)
                                          :quant (m / more-than
                                                :op1 (t3 / temporal-quantity
                                                      :quant 1
                                                      :unit (w2 / week))))))))))

# ::id 6 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

(r / report-01
      :ARG0 (m / media
            :mod (s / state))
      :ARG1 (h / have-concession-91
            :ARG1 (d / damage-01
                  :ARG0 (e / earthquake
                        :location (p / province
                              :name (n / name
                                    :op1 "Sichuan"))
                        :ARG0-of (d2 / devastate-01))
                  :ARG1 (f / facility
                        :mod (s2 / sport))
                  :ARG1-of (s3 / serious-02))
            :ARG2 (ii / injure-01
                  :polarity -
                  :ARG0 e
                  :ARG1 (a / athlete)))
      :time (w / wednesday))

            :ARG1 (c / city
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Shanghai")

                        :ARG1-of (n2 / normal-02)))
            :ARG2 (r / rumor-01
                  :ARG1 (p2 / person
                        :ARG0-of (k / kill-01
                              :mod (s / serial))
                        :ARG1-of (l / loose-03)))))

# ::id 11 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

      :ARG0 (a / authority
            :mod (c / customs))

            :ARG1 (s2 / surplus
                  :mod (t / trade-01
                        :ARG0 (c2 / country
                              :name (n / name
                                    :op1 "France"))))
            :ARG3 (m / monetary-quantity
                  :quant 4000000000
                  :unit (e / euro))
            :ARG4 (m2 / monetary-quantity
                  :quant 1000000000
                  :unit (e2 / euro))
            :time (y / year
                  :mod (l / last))
            :ARG1-of (c3 / cause-01
                  :ARG0 (r2 / rise-01
                        :ARG1 (e3 / euro)
                        :ARG4 (d / dollar))))
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :weekday (f / friday))
      :ARG1-of (c4 / cite-01
            :ARG0 a
            :ARG2 (d3 / drag-01
                  :ARG0 s2
                  :ARG1 (e4 / export-01)
                  :ARG1-of c3
                  :ARG0 r2)))

                                                :name (n / name
                                                      :op1 "Microsoft"
                                                      :op2 "Corp.")))))))))

# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (c / company
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Nomura"
                  :op2 "Holdings"
                  :op3 "Inc.")
            :mod (h / house
                  :mod (s2 / securities))
            :ARG1-of (h2 / have-degree-91
                  :ARG2 (l / large)
                  :ARG3 (m / most)
                  :ARG5 (c2 / country
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Japan"))))
      :ARG1 (w / withdraw-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 c
            :ARG2 (b / business
                  :mod (s3 / securities
                        :ARG1-of (b2 / back-01
                              :ARG0 (m2 / mortgage-01
                                    :mod (r / residential))))
                  :mod c2))
      :time (a / after
            :op1 (l2 / lose-02
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1-of (c3 / cause-01
                        :ARG0 (w2 / worsen-01
                              :ARG1 (m3 / market
                                    :mod m3)))))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (m4 / monday)))

# ::id 1899 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok the pilots of two us fighter jets that mistakenly bombed and killed four canadian soldiers in afghanistan should face administrative punishment but not a court martial , the investigating officer recommended thursday .
# ::alignments
(r / recommend-01
      :ARG0 (o / officer
            :ARG0-of (ii / investigate-01))
      :ARG1 (c / contrast-01
            :ARG1 (r2 / recommend-01
                  :ARG1 (f / face-01
                        :ARG0 (p / person
                              :ARG0-of (p2 / pilot-01
                                    :ARG1 (j / jet
                                          :quant 2
                                          :poss (w / we)
                                          :ARG0-of (f2 / fight-01)
                                          :ARG0-of (b / bomb-01
                                                :ARG1 (s / soldier
                                                      :quant 4
                                                      :mod (c2 / country
                                                            :name (n / name
                                                                  :op1 "Canada")))
                                                :ARG1-of (m / mistake-01))
                                          :ARG0-of (k / kill-01
                                                :ARG1 s)
                                          :location (c3 / country
                                                :name (n2 / name
                                                      :op1 "Afghanistan"))))
                              :ARG1 (p3 / punish-01
                                    :mod (a / administrate-01))))
                  :ARG2 (r3 / recommend-01
                        :polarity -
                        :ARG0 o
                        :ARG1 (f3 / face-01
                              :ARG0 p
                              :ARG1 (c4 / court-martial))))
            :time (d / date-entity
                  :weekday (t / thursday))))

# ::id 1900 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok israeli and moroccan scientists are working together for the first time to research the effects of the moslem fasting month of ramadan on diabetics , the jerusalem post reported sunday .
# ::alignments
(r / report-01
      :ARG0 (p / post-01
            :ARG0 (c / city
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Jerusalem")))
      :ARG1 (w / work-01
            :ARG0 (a / and
                  :op1 (p2 / person
                        :mod (c2 / country
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Israel")))
                  :op2 (p3 / person
                        :mod (c3 / country
                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "Morocco")))
                  :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                        :ARG2 (s / scientist)))
            :ARG1 (r2 / research-01
                  :ARG0 a
                  :ARG1 (e / effect-03
                        :ARG0 (m / month
                              :time-of (f / fast-02
                                    :mod (r3 / religious-group
                                          :name (n4 / name
                                                :op1 "Ramadan")))
                              :mod r3
                              :name (n5 / name
                                    :op1 "Moslem")))
                  :ARG1 (d / diabetics)))
      :mod (t / together)
      :ord (o / ordinal-entity
            :value 1)
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :weekday (s2 / sunday)))

# ::id 1901 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok african union-brokered peace talks between the sudanese government and darfur rebel leaders bogged down again tuesday , barely ## minutes after delegates resumed negotiations following a three-day pause .
# ::alignments
(b / bog-down-01
      :ARG1 (t / talk-01
            :ARG0 (g / government-organization
                  :ARG0-of (g2 / govern-01
                        :ARG1 (c / country
                              :name (n / name
                                    :op1 "Africa"))))
            :ARG1 (p / person
                  :ARG0-of (l / lead-02
                        :ARG1 (r / rebel
                              :mod (c2 / country
                                    :name (n2 / name
                                          :op1 "Darfur")))))
            :ARG2 (p2 / peace)
            :ARG1-of (b2 / broker-01
                  :ARG0 (u / union)))
      :mod (a / again)
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (t2 / tuesday))
      :time (a2 / after
            :op1 (r2 / resume-01
                  :ARG0 (d2 / delegate)
                  :ARG1 (n3 / negotiate-01
                        :ARG0 d2)
                  :ARG1-of (f / follow-01
                        :ARG2 (p3 / pause-01
                              :duration (t3 / temporal-quantity
                                    :quant 3
                                    :unit (d3 / day)))))
            :quant (b3 / barely
                  :op1 t3
                  :quant 1
                  :unit (m / minute))))

                                    :op1 "Honda"))

                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "British"
                                    :op2 "Tobacco"))
                        :op3 (c4 / company
                              :mod (c5 / country
                                    :name (n3 / name
                                          :op1 "America")))))
            :ARG1 (t / team
                  :mod (f / formula
                        :mod (b4 / bar)
                        :ord (o / ordinal-entity
                              :value 1))))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (m / monday)))

# ::id 1903 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

# ::alignments
(a / and
      :op1 (c / condemn-01
            :ARG0 (t / team
                  :mod (o / organization
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "U.N."))
                  :ARG1-of (s / send-01
                        :ARG2 (c2 / country
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Algeria"))
                        :purpose (l / look-into-11
                              :ARG0 t
                              :ARG1 (ii / insurgency
                                    :mod (r / religious-group
                                          :name (n3 / name
                                                :op1 "Muslim"))
                                    :duration (t2 / temporal-quantity
                                          :quant 6
                                          :unit (y / year)))))
                  :ARG1 (e / extremism
                        :ARG0-of (s2 / spur-01
                              :ARG1 (v / violence))))
            :op2 (c3 / call-03
                  :ARG0 t
                  :ARG1 (r2 / rein-in-01
                        :ARG0 (g / government-organization
                              :ARG0-of (g2 / govern-01))
                        :ARG1 (f / force
                              :mod (s3 / security)
                              :poss g))
                  :ARG2 g
                  :mod (a2 / also))))

                                          :op1 "Philippines"))))

                        :op1 (d / date-entity
                              :weekday (f / friday))))

                  :ARG0 m
                  :ARG1 (p2 / person
                        :quant 4))))

            :ARG0 (g / globalize-01)

                  :ARG0-of (c2 / criticize-01)
                  :mod (f / fierce))
            :time (a / always))
      :ARG2 (l / look-02
            :ARG0 (e / expand-01
                  :ARG1 (a2 / and
                        :op1 (t / trade-01
                              :mod (ii / international))
                        :op2 (c3 / cooperate-01
                              :mod (ii2 / international))))
            :ARG1 (p2 / possible-01
                  :polarity -
                  :ARG1 (r / reverse-01
                        :ARG1 e))
            :duration (a3 / at-least
                  :op1 (t2 / temporal-quantity
                        :quant 1
                        :unit (d / decade)))))

      :ARG0 (g / government-organization

      :ARG1 (g3 / grow-01
            :ARG1 (e / economy
                  :mod (c / country
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "U.S.")))
            :ARG2 (p / pace
                  :mod (s / sluggish)
                  :mod (p2 / percentage-entity
                        :value 1))
            :time (q / quarter
                  :mod (f / final)
                  :part-of (y / year
                        :mod (l / last))))
      :time (w / wednesday)
      :manner (r2 / revise-01
            :quant 1
            :ARG1-of (ii / include-91
                  :ARG2 (r3 / revise-01
                        :mod (d / downward)
                        :ARG1-of (h / have-degree-91
                              :ARG2 (s2 / steep)
                              :ARG3 (m / most)
                              :ARG5 (r4 / revise-01
                                    :time (m2 / multiple
                                          :op1 (t / temporal-quantity
                                                :quant 1
                                                :unit (y2 / year)))))))))

                  :ARG0 (t2 / team

                        :weekday (t3 / tuesday)))))
